  "text": "Mutations in EGFR tyrosine kinase are noted in about 15% of NSCLC adenocarcinoma in the Unites States [CITATION_1] and more often in women and non-smokers. In Asian population, the incidence of EGFR mutation is extremely higher, up to 62% [CITATION_2] . Advanced NSCLCs that contains characteristic mutations in EGFR are highly sensitive to EGFR-TKIs (EGFR-tyrosine kinase inhibitors), and hence, considered as a predictor of responsiveness.",
